name: Emily
meaning: Derived from the Roman name Aemilia, which was likely based on the Latin word 'aemulus' meaning 'rival' or 'eager'. It became a popular name in the Middle Ages and has remained so ever since.

name: Lucas
meaning: Derived from the ancient Roman name Lucius, which was derived from the Latin word 'lux' meaning 'light'. It has been a popular name since the Middle Ages, especially after the apostle Luke in the New Testament.

name: Olivia
meaning: Derived from the Latin word 'oliva' meaning 'olive tree'. It became a popular name in the 17th century, likely due to its association with the olive, a symbol of peace and prosperity.

name: Ethan
meaning: Derived from the Hebrew name 'Ethan' meaning 'firm, strong, enduring'. It was a popular biblical name in the Old Testament and has remained a common name in the English-speaking world.

name: Isabella
meaning: Derived from the Hebrew name 'Elisheba' meaning 'devoted to God'. It became a popular name in Europe during the Middle Ages, particularly after the 13th-century Spanish queen Isabella I.

name: William
meaning: Derived from the Germanic name 'Wilhelm', which was composed of the elements 'wil' meaning 'will, desire' and 'helm' meaning 'helmet, protection'. It became a popular name in England after the Norman Conquest in 1066.

name: Sophia
meaning: Derived from the Greek word 'sophia' meaning 'wisdom'. It was a popular name in the Byzantine Empire and has remained a favorite in the English-speaking world.

name: Noah
meaning: Derived from the Hebrew name 'Noach' meaning 'rest, comfort'. It is a biblical name, most famously associated with the hero of the Great Flood story in the Book of Genesis.

name: Emma
meaning: Derived from the Germanic name 'Imma' or 'Emm', which may have been a short form of names beginning with the element 'ermen' meaning 'whole, universal'. It became a popular name in England in the 11th century.

name: Jacob
meaning: Derived from the Hebrew name 'Ya'aqov' meaning 'supplanter' or 'to follow'. It is a biblical name, associated with the twin brother of Esau and the father of the Twelve Tribes of Israel.
